  "text": "We observe regulatory edges in the GRN for T cells between Transcription Factors (TFs) GAT A3, RU N X2 and their target genes, with minimal interaction in B cells and NK cells (Figure 11 ), and indeed these TFs are known to be associated with activation of cytotoxic T cells [CITATION_1] and CD8 T cell development (Woolf et al., 2003) . We also observe cases such as F OS, F OSB with different regulatory functions despite belonging to the same TF family, showing an example of how expression-derived information can further distinguish genetic interactions which cannot be immediately deciphered from epigenetic data.",
